{
  "demo implementation details": {
    "prefix": "demo-impl",
    "body": [
      "# Implementation details",
      "",
      "Let's create a single file CLI tool in @src/main.ts for downloading assets from GitHub releases.",
      "",
      "- register a `validate` and a `download` citty commands",
      "- both accepting two flags:",
      "  - `-f` or `--file` for the config file",
      "  - `-d` or `--dir` for the download location",
      "- read the config file passed into memory",
      "- create a get github token function, that runs the `gh` binary from path with the following command: `gh auth token` captures the output and returns it",
      "- create a substitue file name template function, this receives host arch + os + version strings and runs the nunjucks templating and returns the substituted string",
      "- create a get version function that receives an asset too, if the version is present then it returns that otherwise it makes a github call to idenditfy the latest release and returns that version",
      "- create a get release url function which receives an asset object, templated filename and actual version and returns the release's asset url or throws if we can't find the repo",
      "- create a download asset function that will receive an url and a folder, and downloads the given asset to the folder or throws in case of any error",
      "- make the `main` function orchestrate all the above mentioned logics to a full download flow",
      "",
      "# Configuration File",
      "",
      "- config file can be either json or yaml file, both are valid configuration files",
      "- config file is an array of object with the followin object shape:",
      "  - `org` -> Github organization or user that owns the repository",
      "  - `repo` -> Github repository name",
      "  - `version` -> Optional release tag to pin specific releases, when omitted we use latest",
      "  - `nameTemplate` -> Nunjucks template that expands to the release asset filename",
      "",
      "## Templating Variables",
      "",
      "- `os` -> host system os",
      "- `arch` -> host system arch",
      "- `version` -> resolved github release version"
    ],
    "description": "demo prompt",
    "scope": "markdown"
  },
  "demo json schema": {
    "prefix": "demo-json",
    "body": [
      "## Config Validation",
      "",
      "For config file validation use json schema as a single source of truth, implemented the following way:",
      "",
      "- create a new json schema `ghd.schema.json` that defines the schema of our configuration, with examples and descriptions",
      "- add `ajv` as dependency and import the json schema as json so our bundler bundles it into the release file",
      "- validate the json schema to our @ghd.schema.json using ajv after reading it in",
      "- ignore `$schema` tags in case of json files, they are only there for better IDE support"
    ],
    "description": "demo json schema section"
  },
  "demo testing": {
    "prefix": "demo-testing",
    "body": [
      "# Testing",
      "",
      "For testing make sure every function is unit testable, write mocks for network calls.",
      "",
      "- require `vitest` as a dev dependency for tests",
      "- extend @package.json with a test command to run vitest",
      "- create unit tests for each individual functions, with at least one positive and one negative test case"
    ],
    "description": "demo testing section",
    "scope": "markdown"
  },
  "demo rule": {
    "prefix": "demo-rule",
    "body": [
      "---",
      "paths:",
      "  - \"*.ts\"",
      "  - \"*.js\"",
      "---",
      "",
      "# TypeScript Conventions",
      "",
      "## Commands",
      "",
      "| Command             | What it does                                           |",
      "| ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |",
      "| `npm run lint`      | Lints the codebase with biome and typedoc.             |",
      "| `npm run test`      | Run unti tests on the codebase.                        |",
      "| `npm run typecheck` | Runs the new go typescript compiler for type checking. |",
      "",
      "## Validation",
      "",
      "Make sure that lints, tests and typecheck always passes."
    ],
    "description": "demo ts rule",
    "scope": "markdown"
  },
  "demo linter": {
    "prefix": "demo-biome",
    "body": [
      "{",
      "  \"\\$schema\": \"./node_modules/@biomejs/biome/configuration_schema.json\",",
      "  \"vcs\": {",
      "    \"enabled\": true,",
      "    \"clientKind\": \"git\",",
      "    \"useIgnoreFile\": true",
      "  },",
      "  \"files\": {",
      "    \"ignoreUnknown\": true,",
      "    \"includes\": [\"src/**\", \"*.ts\", \"*.json\", \"*.md\", \"!!**/node_modules\", \"!!**/dist\"]",
      "  },",
      "  \"formatter\": {",
      "    \"enabled\": true,",
      "    \"indentStyle\": \"space\",",
      "    \"indentWidth\": 2,",
      "    \"lineWidth\": 100,",
      "    \"lineEnding\": \"lf\"",
      "  },",
      "  \"javascript\": {",
      "    \"formatter\": {",
      "      \"quoteStyle\": \"double\",",
      "      \"semicolons\": \"asNeeded\",",
      "      \"trailingCommas\": \"all\",",
      "      \"bracketSpacing\": true,",
      "      \"arrowParentheses\": \"always\"",
      "    }",
      "  },",
      "  \"linter\": {",
      "    \"enabled\": true,",
      "    \"rules\": {",
      "      \"recommended\": true,",
      "      \"style\": {",
      "        \"noDefaultExport\": \"error\",",
      "        \"useBlockStatements\": \"error\",",
      "        \"useConsistentTypeDefinitions\": {",
      "          \"level\": \"error\",",
      "          \"options\": { \"style\": \"type\" }",
      "        },",
      "        \"noUselessElse\": \"error\",",
      "        \"noNegationElse\": \"error\",",
      "        \"noCommonJs\": \"error\",",
      "        \"useConst\": \"error\",",
      "        \"useForOf\": \"error\",",
      "        \"useNamingConvention\": {",
      "          \"level\": \"error\",",
      "          \"options\": {",
      "            \"conventions\": [{ \"selector\": { \"kind\": \"objectLiteralProperty\" }, \"match\": \".*\" }]",
      "          }",
      "        },",
      "        \"useShorthandFunctionType\": \"error\",",
      "        \"useTemplate\": \"error\",",
      "        \"noNestedTernary\": \"error\"",
      "      },",
      "      \"complexity\": {",
      "        \"useArrowFunction\": \"error\",",
      "        \"useMaxParams\": {",
      "          \"level\": \"error\",",
      "          \"options\": { \"max\": 5 }",
      "        }",
      "      },",
      "      \"correctness\": {",
      "        \"useSingleJsDocAsterisk\": \"error\"",
      "      },",
      "      \"suspicious\": {",
      "        \"noUnassignedVariables\": \"error\",",
      "        \"noUnusedExpressions\": \"error\",",
      "        \"useAwait\": \"error\"",
      "      },",
      "      \"nursery\": {",
      "        \"noMisleadingReturnType\": \"error\",",
      "        \"noNestedPromises\": \"error\",",
      "        \"useConsistentTestIt\": \"error\",",
      "        \"useErrorCause\": \"error\"",
      "      },",
      "      \"performance\": {",
      "        \"noNamespaceImport\": \"error\"",
      "      }",
      "    }",
      "  },",
      "  \"plugins\": [",
      "    \"./.biome/no-promise.grit\",",
      "    \"./.biome/camel-case.grit\",",
      "    \"./.biome/versions.grit\"",
      "  ]",
      "}"
    ],
    "description": "biome config for the demo",
    "scope": "json"
  },
  "demo grit no promise": {
    "prefix": "demo-grit-no-promise",
    "body": [
      "engine biome(1.0)",
      "language js(typescript, jsx)",
      "",
      "or {",
      "  `\\$_.then(\\$...)`,",
      "  `\\$_.catch(\\$...)`,",
      "  `\\$_.finally(\\$...)`,",
      "} as \\$chain where {",
      "  register_diagnostic(",
      "    span = \\$chain,",
      "    message = \"Prefer async/await over Promise.then/.catch/.finally.\"",
      "  )",
      "}"
    ],
    "description": "grit pattern banning promise chains"
  },
  "demo grit camel": {
    "prefix": "demo-grit-camel",
    "body": [
      "engine biome(1.0)",
      "language json",
      "",
      "JsonMemberName() as \\$name where {",
      "    \\$name <: or { r\".*_.*\", r\".[A-Z].*\" },",
      "    register_diagnostic(",
      "        span = \\$name,",
      "        message = \"JSON keys must use camelCase.\",",
      "        severity = \"warn\"",
      "    )",
      "}"
    ],
    "description": "grit pattern enforcing camelCase json keys"
  },
  "demo grit version": {
    "prefix": "demo-grit-version",
    "body": [
      "engine biome(1.0)",
      "language json",
      "",
      "pair(key = \\$section, value = object(members = \\$deps)) where {",
      "    \\$section <: r\"^\\\"(?:dependencies|devDependencies|peerDependencies|optionalDependencies)\\\"\\$\",",
      "    \\$deps <: contains bubble pair(value = string() as \\$version) where {",
      "        \\$version <: not r\"^\\\"[\\^~]?\\d+\\.\\d+(?:\\.\\d+)?(?:-[\\w.-]+)?(?:\\+[\\w.-]+)?\\\"\\$\",",
      "        register_diagnostic(",
      "            span = \\$version,",
      "            message = \"Dependency version must be exact or use ^/~ and pin at least major.minor (e.g. 1.2.3, ^1.2, ~1.2.3).\",",
      "            severity = \"error\"",
      "        )",
      "    }",
      "}"
    ],
    "description": "grit pattern enforcing pinned package versions"
  },
  "demo npm cmd": {
    "prefix": "demo-npm-cmd",
    "body": [
      ",",
      "    \"typecheck\": \"tsgo --noEmit\",",
      "    \"lint\": \"biome check --fix && typedoc\",",
      "    \"test\": \"vitest run\""
    ],
    "description": "npm scripts for the demo"
  },
  "demo typedoc": {
    "prefix": "demo-typedoc",
    "body": [
      "{",
      "  \"\\$schema\": \"https://typedoc.org/schema.json\",",
      "  \"entryPoints\": [\"src/main.ts\"],",
      "  \"emit\": \"none\",",
      "  \"exclude\": [\"**/*.test.ts\"],",
      "  \"validation\": {",
      "    \"notDocumented\": true,",
      "    \"invalidLink\": true,",
      "    \"notExported\": true",
      "  },",
      "  \"requiredToBeDocumented\": [\"Function\", \"TypeAlias\", \"Interface\", \"Class\", \"Enum\", \"Variable\"],",
      "  \"treatValidationWarningsAsErrors\": true,",
      "  \"logLevel\": \"Warn\"",
      "}"
    ],
    "description": "typedoc config for the demo"
  }
}
